# Writing `.cursor/rules`

Focused, actionable, scoped. Applied via **`alwaysApply`**, **`globs`**, relevance from **`description`**, or **`@rule`**. When editing rules from unrelated files, @mention **`writing-rules`**.

Prefer **specificity > completeness**.

## File format

- **Path:** `.cursor/rules/**/*.mdc` (kebab-case names; subfolders OK).
- **Frontmatter:** valid YAML; camelCase keys.

```yaml
---
description: One short sentence (rule picker + relevance model).
globs: "**/*.ts,**/*.tsx"   # comma-separated, NO spaces after commas
alwaysApply: false         # minimize always-on (<2 tiny rules ideally)
---
```

Only **one** `--- … ---` block. Don’t raw `---` in body prose.

## Size & scope

| Guideline | Target |
| --- | --- |
| Hard cap | < **500** lines (Cursor docs) |
| Sweet spot | < **100**, ideally **< 50** for one topic |
| Topics | One concern per file (split TS vs Svelte vs CSS rather than mega “frontend”) |
| Sources | **`@path/to/File.ts`** or “see **`other-rule.mdc`**” instead of copying stanzas |

## Content

Bullets (“do / don’t”), not essays. Prefer **positive** tiny examples — “❌ BAD” only for recurring regressions.

`description`: concrete (<~80 chars ideal). **`alwaysApply: false`** + vague description ⇒ rule never loads.

Reserve **`alwaysApply: true`** for project-wide invariant(s) (`project-conventions`).

## Anti-patterns

No orphan rules (false + blank globs + useless description). No pasted style guides or giant CLI catalogs. Skip rare-edge essays.

Add/trim rules **when the agent repeats the same mistake** — iterate in git.

## Pre-merge checklist

- [ ] `.mdc` inside `.cursor/rules/`
- [ ] `description` plus `alwaysApply` and/or meaningful `globs`
- [ ] Body < 500 LoC, preferably < 100
- [ ] ≥1 terse positive example where helpful
- [ ] References instead of pasted codebases
